<TITLE> Dhaka stocks rally in midday trade </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 20 (bdnews24.com)  Dhaka stocks rallied in the midday trade Thursday, paced by a rush for buying of power, banks and mutual funds shares. Summit Power led the rally. The fresh buying came after investors had locked in gains in the week's first three trading days. The market had earlier registered a ten-day rally. The DGEN or general index surged 30.81 points or 1.22 percent to 2545.43 at 12:09pm. The DSI or all-share price index stood at 2107. 40, up by 27.23 points or 1.30 percent from the previous day. Turnover stood at Tk 1.17 billion from transaction of 67, 08, 107 shares; and 113 issues gained, 43 fell and 10 remained steady. Power-sector major Summit Power, the most active share until midday, surged to Tk 1490.0 from Wednesday's close of Tk 1460.75. Prime Bank emerged as the second top leader in turnover and traded higher at Tk 795 from Tk 759.5. Having passed through an adjustment phase in the last couple of days, BRAC Bank rose to Tk 1244 from Tk 1234.25. UCBL surged to Tk 4520 from Tk 4454 on hopes of better dividend yields. DESCO edged up to Tk 1160.5 from 1157. Grameen 1 Mutual Fund and AIMS 1st Mutual Fund traded at an all-time high on anticipation of good earnings. Market heavyweights Power Grid Company of Bangladesh, AB Bank and Southeast Bank also traded upbeat. bdne
